        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(restart): add error logging to fire-and-forget restart emissions",
        "body": "## Enhancement\n\n`emitPreparedGatewayRestart()` is async (returns a Promise) but called with `void` from `deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle()` and `armPendingRestartTimer()`, which are synchronous and cannot await it. Previously, any error during restart emission (e.g., failed IPC signal, broken supervisor connection) was silently lost — the gateway might fail to restart without any diagnostic.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added `.catch()` with `restartLog.warn()` to all 7 `void emitPreparedGatewayRestart(...)` call sites\n- Errors during restart emission are now logged with subsystem logger\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Unit tests (60/60 passed):**\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  60 passed (60)\n```\n\n**git diff:** +33/-7 across 1 file. Each call site now:\n```typescript\nvoid emitPreparedGatewayRestart(opts.emitHooks, opts.reason)\n  .catch((err: unknown) => {\n    restartLog.warn(`restart emission failed: ${String(err)}`);\n  });\n```\n\n## AI Assistance\n\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
        "branch": "fix/restart-emission-error-logging",
